From The ecological and evolutionary consequences of systemic racism

Hello! In order to understand how to read and interpret these interactive maps, youll want to understand the metrics that were using.

Holc Grade systematically grades each neighborhood (as defined by historic trends in redlining from 1950) from A to D: - A: Best - B: Still Desirable - C: Definitely Declining - D: Hazardous

Sources:
- https://ncrc.org/holc-health/ - https://ncrc.org/holc

Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) (raster data) is used as proxy measure of vegetation health, cover and phenology (life cycle stage) over large areas. It is calculated using multiple bands from satellite images. Values closer to 1 indicate presence of vegetation, while near-zero values indicate water and the range between is a range from high density or presence of vegetation to no vegetation present.

Birmingham

3 Layers: Holc Grade for each neighborhood, Mean NDVI for each neighborhood, and Total NDVI (shows NDVI for each pixel of area 30m x 30m)
